  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ 395°F/ Gas 6</p><p>Trim the green stalk<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> off the <strong>aubergine<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>, then chop lengthways until you end up with 8 <span class=\"text-danger\">[16]</span> wedges</p><p>Chop each wedge into 3, then add to a baking tray with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 20 min or until golden and tender</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2306-Step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2306-Step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2306-Step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2306-Step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2306-Step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and chop the <strong>ginger</strong>,<strong> garlic </strong>and<strong> shallots </strong>roughly</p><p>Chop the <strong>green</strong> and<strong> red chilli<span class=\"text-danger\">[es] </span></strong>roughly</p><p>Pick the<strong> coriander leaves</strong> from their stalks and set aside for later</p><p>Chop the <strong>coriander stalks</strong> in half</p><p>Add everything to a <strong>food processor</strong> (except the coriander leaves!) and pulse for 10 secs</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2306-Step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2306-Step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2306-Step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2306-Step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2306-Step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Bash the<strong> lemongrass</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong>, remove the tough outer layer<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> and chop the softer inner core roughly</p><p>Zest the <strong>lime<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (grate lightly with a micro-plane or sharp box grater to avoid grating the white pith!)</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped lemongrass</strong> and<strong> lime zest</strong> to the <strong>food processor</strong> with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>water</strong> and blitz to a rough paste – this is your <strong>spice paste</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
